Issues.Body:
Current logic is:

```javascript
function isInsideClientRect(clientRect, x, y) {
    var top = clientRect.top, bottom = clientRect.bottom, left = clientRect.left, right = clientRect.right;
    return y >= top && y <= bottom && x >= left && x <= right;
}
````

but should be `y < bottom` and `x < right` because `right === left + width` and `bottom === top + height`.
This function is used many times in D&D checks and always adds 1 wrong pixel in each direction.

**Environment:**
angular: 8.2.13
material/CDK: 8.2.3
